item.description:
Motivation In the TCCPP discord server, this was a question that was asked recently:
Why does scanf only work when I scan for char before int?
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; int main() { int n; char c; scanf(&#34;%d&#34;, &amp;n); // Code works if I put this line below the other scanf scanf(&#34;%c&#34;, &amp;c); return 0; } It&rsquo;s a simple program to read in a number and char, trivial enough to just use two scanf to read them in, right?
